        {
                        "name": "14.D.1 Carrying capacity of the maritime transport fleet",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 14. Life below water",
                      
                        "priority": "Management of marine areas and resources of the Baltic Sea at various levels of partnership, in particular the research and scientific sector",
                      
                        "definition": "Total cargo capacity of all transport vessels registered in Polish ports or operated in Polish maritime trade, expressed in gross deadweight tonnage (DWT).",
                      
                        "unit": "thous. tonnes",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Maritime transport fleet - vessels used to transport cargo and passengers at sea.Deadweight tonnage (DWT) - the weight of cargo and stores at summer loadline draft in seawater, expressed in tonnes (1,000 kg). The difference in tonnes between the displacement of a vessel at summer loadline draft in water with a specific gravity of 1.025 t/m³ and the total weight of the vessel, i.e., the displacement of the vessel in tonnes without cargo, fuel, lubricating oil, ballast, fresh water and drinking water in tanks, utility items, as well as passengers, crew, and their belongings.",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland",
                      
                        "availability": "Annual data, since 2017",
                      
                        "notes": "Data are presented by the location of the enterprise's registered office, i.e. they are allocated to the territorial unit where the registered office of the enterprise is located, regardless of the place where the economic activity is actually carried out.",
                      
